The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                                 
	Sydney: Belarussian Victoria Azarenka beat Marion Bartoli 6-3, 6-1 in the womens final at the Brisbane International on Saturday to capture her first WTA singles title.    
	Bartolis loss completed a disappointing day for the French in Brisbane after Spanish Davis Cup hero Fernando Verdasco and Czech Radek Stepanek won their semi-finals against French opponents.         
	Sydney: The singles winners of this months Australian Open will each receive $1.4 million, Tennis Australia (TA) said Saturday. TA said it had increased the overall prize money pool by $1.14 million to $23.14 million.         
	Patna: Olympian Neha Aggarwal and defending champion Poulami Ghatak bowed out of the womens singles event, while ace paddler Achanta Sharath Kamal entered the semi-final of the 70th Senior National Table Tennis Championship here Saturday.        
	New Delhi: The sports ministry decided Saturday that the coaches who would train core athletes for the 2010 Commonwealth Games will be appointed initially for only one year. The contracts of these coaches may be extended beyond the one-year period and till the Games depending on a ministry assessment.        
	London: Former champions Renaults 2009 Formula One car has failed a mandatory crash test but the launch will proceed as planned later this month, a team spokeswoman said on Friday.        
	Melbourne: Australian selectors will have to make a difficult decision on whether to include Matthew Hayden among the 25 players to be awarded contracts for the 2009-10 season, in April. Hayden is keen to play in the Ashes series in December but that is possible only if selectors award him a contract.        
	London: Samit Patel has been granted permission by his county side Nottinghamshire to play in the second edition of the Indian Premier League (IPL).          
	Melbourne: Cricket Australia (CA) is planning to introduce a service through which fans can complain against hooligans via text message to the security guards, who would take just minutes to reach the spot and take action against the troublemakers.          
	Calcutta: Arpita Ghosh scored her third century in as many matches as Bengal made 298 for three against Tripura in the Senior Womens Inter-state Two-day Championship in Cuttack on Saturday. Ghosh made 113.
                                                                                                                                                                         
